Common DHCP server problems
    APIPA Automatic Private IP Addressing
    Fallback for no DHCP connections

if all computers on network lose

169.254.0.0 APIPA Address
all network work, local, but no internet connections

Rogue DHCP server
    - multiple servers sending out info

Quick Review:
    - If you get an APIPA address check to see if you are connected to a DHCP server
    - If you are connected to a DHCP server and still get an APIPA address make sure the DHCP serve is working
    - If you get an IP address other than your correct network ID, you may have a rogue DHCP server